# 47f36b0dcc0a4c96ab8647c2491d0ee8
#: ../../admin-guide/transparent-proxy/wccp-configuration.en.rst:140
msgid ""
"Server side transparency should also be used, but it is not as "
"significant. In its absence, however, origin servers may see the source "
"address of connections suddenly change from the Traffic Server address to"
" client addresses, which could cause problems. Further, the primary "
"reason for not having server side transparency is to hide client "
"addresses which is defeated if the Traffic Server host fails."
msgstr ""

